U . S . crude grades ride out to close on firmer note . U . S . crude grades gained all session Tuesday , firming in both sweet and sour markets on sentiment the domestics are the current crude of choice . The price for bringing over Brent and other trans - Atlantic barrels has turned buyers to the home - grown grades , not to mention the lack of foreign crudes recently on offer . Outright crude prices ended slightly weaker in a subdued session , leaving March West Texas Intermediate / Cushing 5 cents lower at $ 22 . 35 - 45 a barrel . American Petroleum Institute stock data , released late Tuesday , was seen bearish for crude and gas , bullish for heat . 
